Create a PHP script to store and display values in an array.
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>PHP Arrays</title>
<style>
body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-color: #f8f9fa; padding: 40px; }
.card { background: white; padding: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); }
h3 { color: #007bff; border-bottom: 2px solid #007bff; display: inline-block; padding-bottom: 5px; }
/* List Styling */
ul { list-style-type: square; color: #555; }
li { margin: 5px 0; font-size: 18px; }
/* Table Styling */
table { border-collapse: collapse; width: 60%; margin-top: 10px; }
th, td { border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px; text-align: left; }
th { background-color: #343a40; color: white; }
tr:nth-child(even) { background-color: #f2f2f2; }
tr:hover { background-color: #ddd; }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<h1 style="text-align:center">PHP Arrays Demonstration</h1>
<!-- 1. INDEXED ARRAY DEMO -->
<div class="card">
<h3>1. Indexed Array (List of Technologies)</h3>
<p><i>Scenario: Storing a list of skills for a resume.</i></p>
<?php
// Declaration
$tech_stack = array("HTML5", "CSS3", "JavaScript", "PHP 8", "MySQL");
// Adding a new item dynamically
$tech_stack[] = "Bootstrap 5";
echo "<ul>";
// Loop through indexed array
foreach ($tech_stack as $tech) {
echo "<li>$tech</li>";
}
echo "</ul>";
echo "<b>Total Technologies: " . count($tech_stack) . "</b>";
?>
</div>
<!-- 2. ASSOCIATIVE ARRAY DEMO -->
<div class="card">
<h3>2. Associative Array (Student Marks)</h3>
<p><i>Scenario: Storing Key-Value pairs where Key=Subject and Value=Marks.</i></p>
<?php
// Declaration Key => Value
$marks = array(
"Web Development" => 90,
"Database Mgmt" => 85,
"Data Structures" => 78,
"Microprocessors" => 82
);
?>
<table>
<tr>
<th>Subject Name</th>
<th>Marks Obtained</th>
</tr>
<?php
// Loop through associative array
// $subject becomes the Key, $score becomes the Value
foreach($marks as $subject => $score) {
echo "<tr>";
echo "<td>" . $subject . "</td>";
echo "<td>" . $score . "</td>";
echo "</tr>";
}
?>
</table>
</div>
</body>
</html>
